text:
Prezentacja:
wylata :), bursztynowe, zmętnione, piana drobna i trwała;
Aromat: 
bardzo silny winny, pod spodem kołaczą się nuty belgijskie
;
Odczucie:
ciało wysokie do średniego, nasycenie wysokie;
Smak: 
najsilniejsze są nuty winne, cierpkie, goryczka, a z tyłu stoi "Belgia";
Ogólnie:
niezły belgijski sour.

Cor de cobre, translúcida, com espuma branca de altas formação e persistência; excelente lacing;
Aroma de cassis e baunilha;
Sabor de mel sobreposto por amargor moderado; retrogosto seco com uma adstringência um pouco desagradável.

OBS: não percebo essa complexidade fenomenal que as pessoas falam; cerveja abaixo da média pra mim, mas o mundo não deve estar errado em aclamá-la.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

UPDATED: OCT 2, 2008 Bottle brewed June 20, 2007 with 6.9% ABV indicated. My least favorite brew labeled Trappist that I have tasted thus far. Aroma was pretty nice but did have a slight off scent of sour milk or something similar (maybe chalk). Pours a beautiful amber-orange with a hazy, but still obviously sparkling content. Head is average size, rock, and only just off white. Flavor of mine was just salty and bitter, no real depth or character. Went down dry and metallicy at the end. It would take a bit of convincing for me to buy this again.
AR: 6; AP: 4; F:5; M:3; O:10; TS: 2.8;

RE:Rate: February 2008 Bottling. Pours with a huge, off-white, foamy head covering a hazy amber body. Aroma is vinous, with brett, sour, with light fruits. Taste is earthy with brett, a bit sour, still one sided, pretty hoppy for a Belgian, and a champagne like grape taste. Lively bubbles with a water like mouthfeel,
